column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Clear day. wind 10 mph - south. some algae in protected areas.
East wind. severe weather warnings. water appears to have some algae build up.
Very light east wind. very little boat and pwc activity.
No fishing or recreational activity.  No algae!
Water cloudy - possibly due to rain. over 4" of rain in past 5-6 days.
Coo NW wind 5-10 mph. no clouds no activity. pair of eagles and loons.
Light breeze hazy.  1 fishing boat 1 loon.
Light breeze hazy.  No human or wildlife activity.
Clear. jet skis and water skiers no wildlife.
Ripples light breeze and clouds.  1 fishing boat pair of loons.
Ripples light NW breeze light clouds.  2 fishing boats and 2 pwc's.
Ripples light clouds.  Very quiet.  No fish.
Light clouds ripples.  1 boat no fish or wildlife.
Light wind ripples and light clouds.  No wildlife 1 pwc 3 fishing boats.
Light wind and ripples cloudy.  1 fishing boat 1 power boat 1 loon.
Ripples.  1 large inboard - bad wake.  No pwc no wildlife. pleasure boats.
Calm.  No pwc some fishing some swimmers. no wildlife.
Lite wind ripples.  Weeds are bad. no pwc 2 fishing boats no swimmers. 1 loon.
Gusty wind 6-12 inch waves.  No pwc 3 fishing boats 1 speed boat. 1 loon.
No wind. no pwc 1 fishing boat. several ducks no loon.
Calm.  No recreational craft 2 fishing boats. 6 seagulls no loons.
Calm. water looks bad no water flow in outlet.  No boats seagulls.
Exact collection time unknown; Partly cloudy- 5 mph SW wind. Boat launch on Hwy 8 East of Essex Rd.
Full sun- blue sky- warm water + lite algae
Heavy rain in morning-Full-Part sun-No algae-Cooler water temp
Slight overcast- windy and no algae..
Overcast- rained all morning- calm + cool water- no algae
Last reading this year- blue sky- lite breeze- brown water- most water plants dead
Almost full sun- slight breeze- approx 67 degs- no boat traffic.. Water seemed cool and clear..
Calm cool water- overcast sky + no boats.
72 degs- steady breeze- almost clear sky- no boat traffic- lots of tree pollen near shore- panfish still on beds.. Water temp. still cool..
78 degs- lite but steady breeze- blue sky with very lite clouds- two other boaters on the water- fish off the beds- water starting to warm up
88 degs.- stiff breeze- partly cloudy- no one on the water- water is getting warm- seems to be alot of dead plant matter (black muck on or near the shore).
S.E. wind-choppy water- partly cloudy- two boats on the water- low 70's.
Blue sky- steady breeze-slight chop to the water- 65 degs- no traffic on lake- very nice start to the day.
Very overcast- grey/dark clouds- little boat traffic- lite breeze- water seems dark.
Partly cloudy- mainly sun- lite breese- 2-3 boats + some sea-do's + a few kayaker's.. The lake is just starting to bloom..
Full sun- steady breeze + choppy water- no one on the lake.
75 degs- clear blue sky- steady breese from south west- choppy water- no one on the lake- very quiet..
Last reading for the year.. Sunny- light breese- lite chop on the water- nice temp.- near 58 degs.- most of the water plants are dead..
Steady NW breeze- no boats- saw the loon's- clear sky and approx 63 deg's..
A steady breeze from the NW- clear skies- no boat traffic- cool air temps. (52 degs)- just a beautiful day..
Steady breeze from the north- mainly sunny- only two boats on the water and just a great day..
Nice sunny day with a lite breeze.. One boat with water skiers + a few kids swimming.. Water temp. is just right for swimming..
Very windy (from the west) sunny and warm.
Sunny (for now)- near 90 degs.- very windy from southwest- choppy waters but the boats still got out to enjoy the day..
Bright sunny day- almost 70 degs. and a steady breeze from SE gives us a choppy surface.. Very few boats out and most docks are in.. Its fall and the readings confirm that..
A few clouds- lite breeze and almost 75 degs. No one on the lake and we still have a few boats/ docks to put in yet.
Slightly overcast- steady breeze from the SE- choppy water (sort of a bad day for reading) but it was nice to get out.  Only one boat on the lake. Very quiet.
Partly cloudy- lite breeze and a few boats out + about..
Mainly sunny- steady breeze with gusts- 78 degs.- a few boaters- just a beautiful day.
Party cloudy- lite breeze from West makes a small chop on the water..  No one on the water today
Clear sunny day- lite breeze with small ripples on the surface.. Looks like two boats and one kayak on the lake..
training day with Sandy- full cloud cover + sprinkles- no boats- 1 loon- several recent rains
partly cloudy- small ripple- no other boats- after 4 cold nights. Al Legler helped with readings
Sunny- small ripples- light Northwest breeze- kayaks- no ski boats- Al Legler assisted
Steady breeze- choppy water with slight over-cast. Only two or three people on the water.
Very calm- sunny morning with 1 pesky skidoo. Day before was active ski day. data taken from kayak.
Clear day- small ripples. Finally a nice day after last week was cold and rainy. Very quit - no boats. many seagulls that migrate through this time of year.
